121
00:14:55,350 --> 00:14:57,420
Aigoo...

122
00:15:03,580 --> 00:15:05,960
My mom probably did it

123
00:15:07,070 --> 00:15:09,770
because she wanted to hurt my father's feelings.

124
00:15:10,980 --> 00:15:13,840
I will talk to my father.

125
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:17,750
I think this is a problem we should fix.

126
00:15:21,990 --> 00:15:26,380
Shi Hyun, come to America with me.

127
00:15:30,150 --> 00:15:32,040
Yes, I will.

128
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:36,720
But first, I have to take care of some things.

129
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:42,200
I want to find what I want to do first. Inheriting the company...

130
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:46,510
doesn't really suit me well and I don't have the confidence to do well either.

131
00:15:46,510 --> 00:15:51,910
You should leave it to a person who's skilled at business. Like my father, or Yeo Min.

132
00:15:51,910 --> 00:15:53,960
Right.

133
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:57,190
There's no need to rush your thoughts.

134
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,760
Mom.

135
00:16:14,850 --> 00:16:17,430
Now, what should I do first?

136
00:16:23,550 --> 00:16:25,140
Tae Hee?

137
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:12,790
For this assignment, I looked into places that look the same as they did in the past, but that have a different feeling to them now.

138
00:17:12,800 --> 00:17:18,550
In 1939, Gudun Station was a strategic location that connected Yangpyeong and Wonjoo.

139
00:17:18,550 --> 00:17:24,040
After the orange subway line was established, it closed down.

140
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:28,820
We'll now look at Gudun Station's current state.

141
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:34,500
Compared to other closed stations that became amusement parks or rail bike courses,

142
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:39,950
from thirty-thousand people, Gudun Station is currently receiving...

143
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:44,460
It is still receiving love.

144
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:49,770
The ceiling of the waiting room, which has been registered in our country's modern cultural foundation,

145
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:54,230
has endured for nearly seventy-seven years,

146
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:57,590
and has a very particular architectural meaning.

147
00:17:57,590 --> 00:17:59,510
One, two, three.

148
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,290
One, two—

149
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:04,540
One, two.

150
00:18:04,540 --> 00:18:09,540
Aigoo, seriously! Look at you acting cool and setting the mood all by yourself!

151
00:18:09,540 --> 00:18:10,900
It hurts!

152
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:14,340
That is it. Thank you.

153
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:29,260
If there are no more questions, we will end the presentation here.

154
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,930
You've worked hard.

155
00:18:35,930 --> 00:18:38,040
Come home.

156
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:41,400
Good-bye!

157
00:18:43,730 --> 00:18:47,300
Tae Hee. Enjoy your meal.

158
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:50,350
Yes, enjoy your meal, too.

159
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:07,010
Wow. Your school's cafeteria food is really delicious.

160
00:19:07,010 --> 00:19:11,510
But don't you think that homemade food is a bit better? Like the pasta that I make, or my eggs.

161
00:19:11,510 --> 00:19:14,040
If not, my ramen.

162
00:19:17,700 --> 00:19:20,470
Is your dad doing well?

163
00:19:20,470 --> 00:19:23,470
Yeah. We chose a date for his surgery.

164
00:19:23,470 --> 00:19:26,980
I sincerely hope that he gets better quickly.

165
00:19:26,980 --> 00:19:33,310
But that's all I want to say to you. Finish eating and go.

166
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:12,770
It's cold, right? Warm clothing brought from home.

167
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:18,360
Public universities are pretty nice. All you need to do is show them your ID and they let you in.

168
00:20:46,600 --> 00:20:48,570
Why do you keep acting like this?

169
00:20:48,570 --> 00:20:50,480
What do you mean?

170
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:24,170
How far are you going to keep following me? Why are you being like this?

171
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:28,590
How far are you going to follow me?

172
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:33,600
Anyway, if you followed me all the way here, just tell me what you want.

173
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:37,370
This is just like how it was when we first met.

174
00:21:37,370 --> 00:21:40,830
Tell me why you're being like this. You know that

175
00:21:40,830 --> 00:21:43,800
